# Rule: writing-style

## Filenames

All filenames: lowercase, kebab-case.
- ✅ `case-content-template.md`, `prompt-plan.md`
- ❌ `CaseContentTemplate.md`, `Prompt_Plan.md`

## Heading hierarchy

- Every doc begins with exactly one `# Title` heading
- Sub-sections use `##`; sub-sub-sections use `###`
- Never skip heading levels

## Tone

- Plain, direct English. Avoid marketing words ("seamlessly", "powerful", "robust")
- Second-person ("you") for instructions
- Present tense for descriptions; future tense only for unbuilt features

## Game terminology in docs

Capitalize these proper nouns exactly as shown:

| Term | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `Applicant` | Subject of a case |
| `FeedPost` | A single social media post |
| `VerdictStamp` | The approval/rejection mechanic |
| `Case` | One complete investigable unit |
| `Clue` | A tagged discrepancy |

## Prompts and task descriptions

- State the deliverable in the first sentence
- List constraints before listing steps
- Cite specific filenames (`scripts/state.js`) not vague references ("the state file")
- Number steps if order matters
